ed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ramamotuhu", "text_ar": "رَمَمْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[“ I ate it ”]: (Bd ibid.:) its pl. is in most instances"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^arim~aA='u", "text_ar": "اَرِمَّا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[when it is used as a subst. or as an epithet], like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adil~aA='u", "text_ar": "اَدِلَّا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daliylN", "text_ar": "دَلِيلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aqoribaA='", "text_ar": "اَقْرِبَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qariybN", "text_ar": "قَرِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rimaAmN", "text_ar": "رِمَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also occurs [when it is used as a subst., for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rim~apN", "text_ar": "رِمَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", of which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rimaAmN", "text_ar": "رِمَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a pl., or when it is used as an epithet], like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kiraAmN", "text_ar": "كِرَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kariymN", "text_ar": "كَرِيمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) or you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEoZumN ramaAy^imu", "text_ar": "اَعْظُمٌ رَمَايِمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ramiymN", "text_ar": "رَمِيمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also; or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ramiymN", "text_ar": "رَمِيمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may have the meaning of a gen. n., and therefore be used in the place of a pl. (M.) It is said in the Kur ubi suprà,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mano yuHoyiY A@loEiZaAma wahiYa ramiymN", "text_ar": "مَنْ يُحْيِى ا@لْعِظَامَ وَهِىَ رَمِيمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Who will quicken the bones when they are old and decayed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.?]; the last word being without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because it is a subst., as expl. above, (Ksh, Bd, Jel,) not an epithet; (Ksh, Jel;) or because it is used in the sense of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mafoEuwlN", "text_ar": "مَفْعُولٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as stated above; (Bd;) or because words of the measures"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEiylN", "text_ar": "فَعِيلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEuwlN", "text_ar": "فَعُولٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are sometimes used alike as masc. and fem. [and sing.] and pl., like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SadiyqN", "text_ar": "صَدِيقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rasuwlN", "text_ar": "رَسُولٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaduw~N", "text_ar": "عَدُوٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) And Hátim, or some other, says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A^amaA waAl~a*iY laA yaEolamu Als~ir~a gayoruhu\n                      \n                     \n                        wayuHoyiY AlEiZaAma AlbiyDa wahoYa ramiymu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "now surely, by Him beside whom none knoweth the secret, and who quickeneth the white bones when they are old and decayed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]; in which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rmym", "text_ar": "رميم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may have the meaning of a gen. n., as observed above. (M.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (assumed tropical:)  Anything"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "old and decayed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "worn out."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHoyaY ramiyma AlmakaArimi", "text_ar": "اَحْيَى رَمِيمَ المَكَارِمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He revived what had become decayed of generous qualities"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "actions"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "practices"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "remains of the herbage of the next preceding year:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lh, M:) from the same word in the sense first expl. above. (M.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ramiymu", "text_ar": "رَمِيمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is one of the names of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The east,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "easterly, wind;"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlS~abaA", "text_ar": "الصَّبَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and is also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a proper name for a woman."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "M", "Msb", "K", "TA", "Ksh", "Bd", "Jel", "Lh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}